==English==
===Noun===
'''beauty''' ([[uncountable]] and [[countable]]; ''plural:'' [[beauties]])

#the property, quality, or state of being that is both attractive, pleasing, fine, or good looking, and hopeful [[comeliness]]
#someone that is [[beautiful]]
#something that is particularly good

===Antonyms===
* (''property, quality''): [[despair]], [[disappointment]], [[ugliness]]

===Synonyms===
* (''property, quality''): [[gorgeousness]], [[inspiration]], [[loveliness]]

===Example usages===
* '''1988:''' "… '''beauty''' and recollection, like danger, glamour, greed, hunger- everything but disappointment and desire- were concepts belonging to other people.”  -''Second Son'', Robert Ferro
* ''What a goal, what a beauty''

====Related terms====
*[[beautiful]]
*[[Sleeping Beauty]]

